Show HN: Weird brandon – Stable Diffusion-generated Joe Bidens
text:
I've been working with stable diffusion for an upcoming course I'm developing with my PhD advisor, and in the course of that we wanted to talk about the effects of modifiers on the prompts w.r.t. the generated images.

I put this site together as a demo of the effects of randomly selected modifiers on a single well-represented figure in the stock stable diffusion model's training data, Joe Biden, as a riff on the "dark Brandon" meme that's been going around.

The source is available at https://github.com/pkage/weirdbrandon

Ask HN: Tips for Building Health Informatics
text:
Hey all. My team is building population health and operational quality measures reporting for healthcare providers in medically underserved areas.

We want to map data into the FHIR data standard, because we find that it can be quite useful for very descriptive organization of data.

Has anyone worked in the area of determining the appropriate terminologies/codesets to map to? How do ya'll manage conducting descriptive analytics over data fields where multiple terminology sets may be in-use to describe the same concept?
